    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p>Starting at 9th level, you can incorporate restorative reagents into some of your works:</p><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">Whenever a creature drinks an <i>experimental elixir</i> you created, the creature gains temporary hit points equal to [[/r 2d6]] + your Intelligence modifier (minimum of 1 temporary hit point).</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You can cast @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.bc0gULngyESb3CEo] without expending a spell slot and without preparing the spell, provided you use @item[alchemist's supplies|PHB] as the spellcasting focus. You can do so a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</li></ul></div>",
